title: fanoutqa: What were the construction costs for each of the five largest power stations in the world? (7d96e121dc56676d)

chat_history.content: What were the construction costs for each of the five largest power stations in the world?

The five largest power stations in the world, as of 2023, are:

1. Baihetan Hydroelectric Power Station, China: Construction costs are estimated at $16.6 billion.

2. Three Gorges Dam, China: Construction costs were approximately $43.4 billion.

3. Itaipu Dam, Brazil/Paraguay: The total cost of construction was roughly $19.6 billion.

4. Guri Dam, Venezuela: Construction costs were around $6.6 billion.

5. Xiluodu Dam, China: Estimated construction costs are $6.4 billion.

Note: These costs are often estimated and can vary depending on the sources and the year of reference, given factors like inflation and currency exchange rates.

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.
